                    <h3>Understanding the challenge:<br />What problems are we here to solve? What do we have to work with?</h3>
                    <p>I begin by asking questions and diving deep into both businesses and user goals for the project.</p>

                    <p>As I go, I use a quadrant system where where I document:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Solvable problems - business and user needs that we're addressing</li>
                        <li>Goals and KPIs - key performance indicators - outcomes that we should get if we're successful</li>
                        <li>Questions - areas for exploration, clarification and research</li>
                        <li>Quick wins and opportunities to elevate - often a brief points to ways to address our challenge quickly and easily. I keep track of these ideas while looking for places where we can go from just solving a problem to delivering a superior experince. </li>
                    </ul>

                    <p>What starts as a page in my sketchbook will later become a living document that I share with teams and stakeholders. It lets me get feedback and keep in alignment with business goals and deliverability while always advocating for better customer experience.</p>
                </div>

            </div>

        </div>
        
    </div>

</section>

