                    <h3>Research</h3>
                    <p>I go on to collect as much data as possible about the problem space, with additional methods like:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>competitive and cross-industry analysis - to identify conventions and already-solved
                            problems, as well as looking for opportunities to stand out
                        </li>
                        <li>interviews - drawing on my journalism background speaking with stakeholders, users and
                            partners to turn their individual expertise into tribal knowledge my team can build on</li>
                        <li>analytics - to identify metrics we can use to see what’s already working (and not)</li>
                        <li>user testing - I test existing solutions, if applicable, or even similar products from other
                            companies</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p>Research has to stay scrappy and efficient, since everyone's on deadlines. Luckily, sites like
                        usertesting.com make it easy to run tests quickly, so we never have to move forward without a
                        plan.
                    </p>

                </div>

            </div>

