                    <h3>UI Design: Building Visual Systems</h3>
                    <p>Depending on the situation, the next stage can mean pulling in existing components from a shared
                        pattern library, or creating new visual language. Either way, I’m looking to build out a system,
                        not
                        just a series of one-offs, and if it’s new, test it and prove that it works.</p>
                    <p>My background in illustration and lifelong obsession with knobs, sliders and control panels give
                        me a
                        great foundation to apply to designing user interfaces. One of my favorite challenges is
                        creating UI
                        elements that are satisfying to work with and so immersive, the user doesn’t think about the
                        tool,
                        they just pick it up and use it to get a job done. I’ve had great successes in this area with
                        projects like Cleartune, AnalogKit and Live Activity Maps.</p>
                </div>

            </div>

