                    <h3>Production and Final Polish</h3>
                    <p>My design process doesn’t end at uploading mocks to Zeplin or InVision. There’s a great deal of
                        polish and attention to detail that happens as a product is being built. Microinteractions make
                        the
                        difference between a product that feels okay and a product that feels amazing and seamless and
                        that’s what I’m the most excited about lately.</p>
                    <p>I believe that the future is doing design in the native language of a product and that’s why I
                        recently spent two months at Code Fellows expanding my Javascript skills (adding to 10+ years of
                        CSS). My hope is to move into the emerging niche of product designers who can prototype and
                        design
                        in native code then work closely with (or on) engineering teams where the final phase of the
                        design process is
                        happening. In the meantime, I’m extremely well-equipped to work with engineering teams or design
                        teams to elevate the quality of our final products.</p>

